<br>
&quot;Well, the time has come, so I guess I should just blurt it out and get it over with.  After getting into one too many arguments with the Gods of this realm, I finally came to the painful conclusion that I cannot coexist with them.  I have left Norrath.  I wanted to give myself some time to see if my feelings would soften, but they have not.  I don't think it's fair to my patrons to leave this place without a dedicated owner to keep everything polished and to make sure the drinks don't get watered down.  So it looks like it's time to put the bar up for sale.&quot;<br>
<br>
Drixa puts a hand up.  &quot;No, don't start thinking I'm going to actually 'sell' the Hero Heart.  How could I put an amount on something that was always a labor of love?  But then again, I don't want to cheapen this place by saying I'm just going to give her away either.  What I'd really like to do is pass her on to another person for the donation of a bit of their heart.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;If anyone thinks they have the heart and the time to spare, please contact me by carrier pigeon.  Those pesky birds can find me at jlherr@mindspring.com.  I'd like to hear how you'd like to see the bar form and what redecoration you'd like to do.  Then of course, I'll have to run it past the Gods of this board.&quot;<br>
<br>
Drixa turns and walks quickly away. <p>Drixa<BR>
